WFWorkflowActionParameters.WFTextActionText:
1. Spend the first 15–20 minutes at the beginning of each week to reflect on your progress from the past week and gather insights to improve this week.
2. Define what a "win" looks like for the week ahead with 3–5 big picture goals.
3. Translate each weekly goal into smaller, actionable tasks throughout the week.
4. Keep your plan dynamic and realistic―Add/adjust action items during the week. Reassess priorities midweek if needed.
5. ⭐️ Measure progress, not results―Focus on consistency of action (input) over outcome (output). Score yourself on execution rate: What % of planned tasks have been done?

(1) Roll over unfinished, important tasks to this week.
(2) Drop or delete anything that no longer matters.

✔️ Review reminders
✔️ Review journals
✔️ Review dashboard

✔️ Reread weekly review notes from the past 4 weeks.
✔️ Review [Deep-Work-Machine](https://github.com/huaminghuangtw/Deep-Work-Machine).
✔️ Think Hour: Go to a coffee shop or new environment, bring a journal and pen, leave your phone and laptop at home. Think and journal on bigger picture questions about your life, direction, and daily actions.
• My "🧐 Past Year Review + 😉 Annual Planning" process naturally shifted from focusing on _what I wanted to accomplish_ to emphasizing _how I wanted to be_.

✔️ Review journals (tags)
✔️ Review periodic review notebook
✔️ Review memories in photos
✔️ Review calendar
✔️ Write down "❌ Never Again List" ¹ & " ✅ Double Down List" ²
✔️ Ask myself questions from the "💭 Journal Prompt" list

1. Stop X → Start Y, Things I want to minimize, What do I wish I'd done less of?
2. Go All-In, Things I want to maximize, What do I wish I'd done more of?
